    "As described above, the processing of special categories of data cannot be ruled out for LLMs.",
    "Although the hurdles of article 9(2) are high, but the \"made public\" provision of article 9(2)(e) can also be considered here.",
    "Others argue for a teleological reduction of article 9(1) for anonymisation (Hornung & Wagner, 2020).",
    "Neither variant constitutes an infringement of data subjects' rights where training data has been anonymized.",
    "These complex considerations alone show that there are gaps between the individual-based approach of the GDPR and the tools required for adequately regulating generative AI."
